Republic Savings and LoanAssociation and &lt;Pioneer Savings> of Racine, Wis., said theyhave signed a definitive agreement to combine the twoassociations into a publicly held holding company to be calledRepublic Capital Group Inc.    The associations said they would form the company byexchanging Republic's stock for shares in the holding company,which Pioneer savers could purchase when Pioneer converts frommutual to stock ownership.    The associations added that they would remain independent,but wholly owned, units of the holding company.    The associations said they would continue to do businessusing their present names and management.    The combination of Republic's 459 mln dlrs in assets withPioneer's 125 mln dlrs would make the new holding company thefifth largest savings and loan organization in Wisconsin, theysaid.    The associations said the move is subject to approval bythe Federal Home Loan Bank Board and the Wisconsin Commissionerof Savings and Loan, as well as Republic's shareholders andPioneer's depositors. Reuter&#3;